            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "you can always use the option `desc` to add a binding description\n```\nvim.keymap.set({'n', 'x', 'o' }, 'n', 'h', { desc = 'move_cursor_left' } )\nvim.keymap.set({'n', 'x', 'o' }, 'e', 'j', { desc = 'move_cursor_down' } )\nvim.keymap.set({'n', 'x', 'o' }, 'i', 'k', { desc = 'move_cursor_up' } )\nvim.keymap.set({'n', 'x', 'o' }, 'o', 'l', { desc = 'move_cursor_right' } )\n```\n\nIt's not the same thing but it gives you an actual description of what the binding it's doing/suppose to do",
