            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> would it be possible for me to make a plugin with definitions and upstream it?\n\nWhat definitions? \"Upstreaming\" it means we now have to maintain this new set of definitions. But you haven't made a strong case for it. Convenience aliases introduce a new concept that divides the existing vim approach, increases documentation, confuses discussions. \n\nIt always helps to start by describing the actual problem. The problem is that `j` is very terse name for a command. Knowing the normal-command language is a required part of using vim, but I can imagine some ways to improve it without introducing a new concept: ship a normal-command parser that understands the meaning of a key sequence (macro), and we could provide LSP-like hovers/annotations. https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/19918 https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/18750\n\nOTOH, AI could help with both directions:\n\n- describe a set of actions, get a key sequence\n- input a key sequence, get a description of actions",
